### 0. Check AI service health
GET http://localhost:4004/chat/aiHealth

### 1. Create a conversation
POST http://localhost:4004/chat/createConversation
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Real AI test",
  "agentType": "auto"
}

### 2. Send a CAP question (should auto-route to cap agent)
POST http://localhost:4004/chat/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "ba79ee27-de62-4b0c-8595-f0c348980d6d",
  "message": "Create a CAP entity for Books with title, author, ISBN, and stock",
  "agentType": "auto"
}

### 3. Send a follow-up (tests memory!)
POST http://localhost:4004/chat/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "ba79ee27-de62-4b0c-8595-f0c348980d6d",
  "message": "Now add a service that exposes only available books (stock > 0)",
  "agentType": "auto"
}

### 4. Send a UI5 question (should route to ui5 agent)
POST http://localhost:4004/chat/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "ba79ee27-de62-4b0c-8595-f0c348980d6d",
  "message": "Show me a UI5 view that displays these books in a table",
  "agentType": "auto"
}

### 5. View all messages with metadata
GET http://localhost:4004/chat/Messages?$orderby=createdAt asc&$select=role,content,agentUsed,modelUsed,tokensUsed